        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Electroretinogram recordings show that mice lacking the beta2 subunit of calcium channels have severe deficits in light responses associated with synaptic transmission from photoreceptor to bipolar cells for both cones and rods.. Experimental description: Methods: Mice carrying a disrupted version of one of the four β subunits of VDCCs were studied." ;
